\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 60. R. millii }Boiss. & Heldr. in Boiss.,{\i  Fl. Or. }{\b 1}: 35 (1867). Like {\b 59} but tubers ovoid; honey-leaves 7-12, oblong-ovate; achenes c. 2 mm; beak strongly hooked, c. ¼ as long as the achene. {\i Dry hills. • S. Greece. }Gr.
