\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 66. R. subhomophyllus }(Halácsy) Vierh.,{\i  Österr. Bot. Zeitschr.}{\b  84}:131 (1935) ({\i R. cadmicus} auct., non Boiss.). Slender, not or little-branched, more or less glabrous perennial, with oblong tubers. Basal leaves orbicular or wider than long, 3-sect to base; segments with obtuse lobes. Flowers 1 or 2; honey-leaves 5-7 mm. Achene longer than the slender, hooked beak.{\i  Rocky places on limestone. S. Aegean region.} Cr Gr.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 67. R. incomparabilis }Janka,{\i  Österr. Bot. Zeitschr.}{\b  22}: 174 (1872). Like {\b 66} but tubers cylindrical to fusiform; stems unbranched; leaves 3-sect to c. 4/5; honey-leaves 7-9 mm, broader; achene with longer hooked beak. 2n = 16.{\i  Damp rock-ledges and crevices on schist and granite. • C. part of Balkan peninsula.} Bu Gr Ju.
\par 

