\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 68. R. sprunerianus }Boiss.,{\i  Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  1}({\b 1}): 64 (1843). Much-branched, patent-pubescent to subglabrous perennial, with cylindrical tubers. Basal leaves orbicular-cordate, 3- to 5-fid. Flowers numerous. Achenes with tubercle-based hairs; beak about as long as the achene, nearly straight but hooked at apex. 2n = 16, 32.{\i  Balkan peninsula and Aegean region.} Bu Cr Gr Ju Tu.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 69. R. asiaticus }L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 552 (1753) ({\i Cyprianthe asiatiea} (L.) Freyn). Pubescent perennial with tuberous roots. Outer basal leaves 3-lobed and dentate; inner 3-sect; segments stipitate, pinnatisect. Flowers 30-50 mm in diameter; honey-leaves white, less often yellow, red or purple. Head of achenes c. 10 mm. Achenes ovate, attenuate into a wide, hooked beak. 2n = 16.{\i  S. Aegean region.} Cr Gr.
